trilineal at all, because the problem is that men don't have power or status.  They are depressed in a hierarchical system. The African Guyanese are orientated towards e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11867278 
ducation and social mobility.  People l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 ike the Hope Town Chairman T.T. Thompson, school headmaster, member of the legislature, etc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid11867278 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  were symbols of success and also had power in the churches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 The Indian men are different because their communities are hermetically sealed. Their men with prestige are local mill owners or religious leaders, and all these are men.

