extremely sincere, very well read, neither ruthless nor ostentatious.  Chicago-trained dentist, and his wife Janet from Chicago, a nurse, Jewish.  They tried to live by their creed, never had servants, at parties han
ded out the drinks themselves.  Janet an excellent organiser, at one time Minister of Education, but did not have his oratorical flair.  Cheddy coming back from visits overseas would be stopped at the edge of Georgetown by huge crowds, and make speeches a
bout world events.
