British suspension of the constitution in 1953 on the eve of independence a shameful period.  Has been looking at newly-released documentation.  Has collected notebooks of newspaper clippings.  Remembers after Cheddy's second victory, a 
victory dance at a Georgetown hotel, with Indians and Africans, Portuguese and Chinese all together, even though Burnham had already split off.  Imposing proportional representation to keep him out was ludicrous.  Jagan was no threat.  As absurd as the Am
erican invasion of Grenada.
