\par Wanted to stay in Jamaica, both kids born there, always very happy there.  Living on campus in Mona.  But rising nationalism.  Not attacked himself, but George Comper, English economist married to a Jamaican, driven out.  Felt the department was being mis
managed.  Received offers from McGill (created a special chair) and Chicago, UWI did offer personal chair, but decided to leave, choosing Chicago.  Came in 1966, somewhat reluctantly.
