Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  had met in Cambridge.  Great man, real
 intellectual, now too neglected.  But personally humble.  Schneider, Geertz and Fallows had all worked with him at Harvard; and like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 , all trying to relate social structure, history and culture theoretically.  Parsons had belonged to Malinowski's L
SE seminar, and he did know about Marx, although he neglected them.  Weber and Marx were closer than vulgar Marxists suggest.  Parsons was also well-read in Freudian psychology}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid9330635 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 
