Diane Austin and Nancy Foner went on to do more intensive community studies of where they were working, and kept their own in-depth material.  Jack Alexander took a middle class area of Kingston, and did maybe 12 case studies only, but in much more depth,
 sometimes 20 interviews with one person.  Jack Alexander wro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid5710883 te Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
D at Chicago, but unpublished; a very thorough, quiet, narrowly focussed man.  The others did not do such detailed studies.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
