\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Intention was to refute the idea of disorganisation as the main principle of West Indian kinship.  Difficult in USA where dominant class is orientated towards the nuclear family.  But in l
ast 25 years a general move towards breakdown of nuclear family and rise of female-headed households.  Not uncritical of West Indian men who father children and then take off.  But it is another way of organising.  Does not think in white grandparents wil
l
 play the role they do in black families; they are more likely to use welfare or pension schemes.  Does not expect a recapturing of kinship solidarity in highly individualistic American or European societies.  Chicago black families still send children ba
ck to the South to be brought up by grandparents, but that will erode over time as rural family structures decline.
