\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Knew Schneider from Berkeley in late 1950s.  Geertz and Fallows were also there then.  And Rene Millan, Marxist arch
aeologist, and Robert Murphy, who went to Columbia.  Tried to form a department at Berkeley focussing on these issues, but too much conservative resistance, such as George M. Foster, so the core group moved to Chicago.  Also }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11304545\charrsid13904672 recruited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  Stanley Tambiah, now at Harvard, but did best work at Chicago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 David Schneider had done middle class study in Chicago, and then in the late 1980s with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  got money to extend to a lower class study, ostensibly on teenage pregnancy.  Not very successful.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  has 28 case studies from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 There had been a gap.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 became }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
chairman of department for six years from 1975 and later two other years, including move between buildings, very time-consuming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Previously, had returned for almost a year 
in 1975.  Chandra Jayawardena was now at McQuarrie.  Hoped to collaborate, met in Trinidad, but Chandra didn't stay.  So with Flora returned to live in Hope Town for five months, renting a house which had been built as a brothel.  Found out what had happe
ned to every individual since the 1950s, people, land tenure, etc.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
 has all this material.  Then went on to spend five months in Windsor Forest, collecting similar material.  The boys came for their holidays.
\par 
\par He coded both the Hope Town and Windsor Forest data, linking changing households }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11304545 with individual trajectories.  He s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 till has these except for one tape now missing due to mistake in copying.  Published some of findings in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 West Indian Kinships}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 .  Not collecting genealogies - a restudy.  
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16078451 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Some dra
matic changes had happened in Windsor Forest.  In 1956, had been a rice farming community of small acreages, hand-transplanted, milled in 18 small mills.  In 1975 many new varieties of rice, fertiliser, tractors, no hand-transplanting, a new rice-processi
ng silo. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Many women working in Georgetown factories - but giving their earnings to their fathers or husband, so the relative independence of the women not evident.  Much migration abroad, especially to Canada.  Many Indians going into higher education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Religious factionalism had been largely replaced by political factionalism. (Book on this by woman from McGill, on Bush Hut, adjacent to Hope Town.)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Younger women beginning to be more independent, but there had been a lot of marital instability before: arr
anged marriages would break up, and the girls return home and take up with a man in their own village.  The women were always more autonomous than in India.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Coded cards on individual trajectories: originally analysed in SPSS.  Fay Booker has now converted the tapes to D-base files.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Physical anthropology has now been dropped from the department.  Regards it as a bogus subject.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Favours anthropology stressing feminist issues, but does not believe in feminist an
thropology any more than in gay anthropology.  Has worked successfully with women students.  Was criticised by Verena Stalkey, but she became a friend, and eventually they edited a book together.  Went to first meeting of a large programme on women in the
 Caribbean, but no subsequent involvement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Became interested in computing as soon as first IBM PC was introduced, early 1980s.  Built a Heathkit PC himself, as a hobby.  Son in computing.  Got the department computerised early, despite resistance.  Early w
ork on genealogies on main frame, with hundreds of punch cards.  SPSS.  Late at night and early morning, to save money.  Had learnt much on survey research from Israeli demographer in Ghana.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Next project, late 1980s, on urban poverty, with William J. Wils
on, sociologist, had written on poverty and race, himself black. Earlier research on poverty mainly at Wisconsin.  Proposal linked with National Opinion Research Center (NORC).  Combined a large survey of four `ethnic groups' - black, white, Mexican and P
uerto Rican - with ethnography, run by Smith, but which Wilson wanted to illustrate the results of the survey, while Smith }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid5471589 wanted the ethnography first, to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  determine the significant questions.  Much resulting argument.  But some of the graduate students did
 understand ethnography, including a student of Bourdieu.  So did ethnographic case studies, and also a small independent `Social Opportunities Survey', based on the Jamaican lo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid5471589 
cating surveys.  Data is on loan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 , and raw files are in Data Archive in Social Science Research Computing.  This project took up until he retired in 1995.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Wilson very pig-headed, fixed ideas, very successful, has gone on to Harvard.  He believed the problems of the black population because socially isolated, but studies showed they w
ere not isolated, and many had middle class relatives.  Real problem was lack of jobs.  Roseland in SE Chicago was a prosperous community of blacks and Hispanics until the steel industry collapsed, then quickly an area of poverty and crime.  Such simplist
ic explanations very annoying. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Had earlier plan of linking survey and ethnography with Der}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid5471589 ek Gordon, had been Jamaican Ph}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 D student, worked on Guyanan project, but he died.  Also earlier, mixed methods project to look at macro system of social status and m
obility in Guyana: social mobility survey, case studies of professions, kinship, etc.  This involved Derek Gordon and also Sarah Graham.  Kassim Bacchus worked on Education (now in Canada).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Proved impossible because Burnham had become much more autocratic, dangerous, so decided to move out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Chicago project included a sub-sample of in-depth information as part of quantitative survey, but his idea was to do it the other way round.  Qualitative data is hard to analyse.  Has experimented with ATLAS and NUDIST.  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Most surveys of lower-class black families fail because they assume that the nuclear family with married couple and children is normal, and everything else is deviant.  Vivid memory of interviewing in Guyana, cocks crowing, woman working a sewing mach
ine, children crying, daughter of a clergyman, yet four children by three men, yet she saw this as just a fact of live.  Family not concerned about marriages.  She thought the questions bizarre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Diane Austin, Professor of Anthropology and Sydney Universit
y, has written on women and Pentecostalism in Jamaica.  He now finds this religious stuff depressing, because it saps the energy of the poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Simey very unfortunate influence in establishing the idea that the idsorganised family is the root of poverty.  B
ig, tall, blustering, domineering.  Madeleine Kerr.  Simey's book fitted in well with the ideology of the Jamaican middle class.  But they have long practised a similar family stem, which goes back to slavery and Edward Long, of parallel marriage and mist
ress, the dual marriage system.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13904672 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
\par Fernando Henriques was one of his examiners, with Lucy Mayer, and told }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
 he should not have just studied the lower class.  Henriques an upper class Jamaican, his ethnography good, and the overall idea of relating colour and class.  Affable man.  He became professor at Leeds and later wrote on sex.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Believes firmly in integrating quantification and qualitative material.  Quantification of error: starting from the wrong assumptions, then manipulating and `cleaning' the da
ta to remove inconsistencies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Became interested in archiving fieldwork material when had to move offices.  Problem of what to do with material of Norman McQuarren on Mayan languages: decided to scan much of it.  But most anthropologists do not think their
 fieldwork material should belong to the public domain.  Lloyd Warner burnt all his.  Eric Wolf's wife did support archiving, at Werner Grun Foundation publicised this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Need to start with the younger generation, teach them to collect information electroni
cally.  A computer is more than a typewriter.  Uses ASSAM a lot, a free-form database, can index every word in a file.  This is not being done.  Anthropologists regard fieldnotes as personal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Are there famous re-studies?  Oscar Lewis and Redfield was more
 infamous.  Lewis did not use Redfield's notes.  Criticism of Mead is not based on her notes, but on re-interviewing her informants.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  and Schneider wanted to restudy Yankee City, but found Lloyd Warner had destroyed his field records.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  did give Eric Handley access to all his own Windsor Forest material, but didn't publish much from it, and became rather secretive about his own material.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 In Hope Town and Windsor Forest }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid8336828 Raymond}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672  was trying a kind of longitudinal follow-up, but anthropologists 
do not get the funding to do continuous large scale studies.  The poverty study with Wilson cost millions of dollars for a NORC survey of 3,500 individuals, and the data not reliable.  Interviewers got low response from black community.  Did much better w
h
ere used own graduate students as interviewers.  Suspects a lot of professionals just made up the answers.  Has observed this with the Census.  They get answers through neighbours, skip a lot.  Need three or more interviews before people will talk in dept
h, e.g. about their history of sexual unions.  Survey interviews demand pre-programmed answers.  This is why good interviewers will write notes in the margins.  These can conflict with the quantitative findings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Hope for new generation who do research using computers and free form databases.  But not being taught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 
Verification not possible through reinterviewing an earlier informant, as with Mead.  Can look at fieldwork notes, but not sure that Malinowski's diaries influence how you would interpret his the
ory of culture - which was wrong from the start.  With Meyer Fortes, his material on the Tallensi so well worked out in his monograph that the originals might not add much.  But it is hard for somebody else 20 years later to read the notes and put themsel
ves in that situation and understand all the unwritten clauses in the fieldnotes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 But has started to write an account of Hope Town as it was in the 1950s, drawing in part on own fieldnotes, because there is a man he knew there as a boy, who went to England
, joined the army, married a teacher and returned, and they have set up a museum in their house.  Doesn't know what people would make of  his fieldnotes.  Not as well organised as Audrey Richards, who at Malinowski's advice put hers on big sheets of paper
.  Anthropologists tend to be less well organised than that.  Did evolve large card system for genealogical study.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid16078451 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid13904672\charrsid13904672 Best thing in life getting to know the Caribbean and its history.  Worst thing academic bureaucracies.  Ghana an interesting interlude.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid13904672 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid919843\charrsid13904672 
